records.addlTxt:
Defendant Amonte Damon Hamilton in court with attorney William Joseph Reddin.  Grant Ian Huebner appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SES.
 Court conducts conference with counsel in chambers. Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing. 

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS AND 6 MONTHS, with credit for 70 DAYS time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR 6 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR.  
The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and IS eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program". 

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 18 MONTHS.  
Court orders the following conditions of probation and extended supervision:
*Serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction, with huber release for: work and child care (report date: 4/7/2017);
*No weapons;
*No new offenses;
*Maintain regular employment;
*Absolute Sobriety.

Court orders restitution set at $0.  
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.   
As to all costs and surcharges, Court orders amounts to be paid during period of probation. If revoked, Court orders DOC shall collect prison funds at an amount or percentage deemed appropriate by the Department of Corrections.  Remaining balance to be collected during the period of extended supervision.  Unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment.  

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm, body armor or ammunition.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court advised defendant of his right to seek post conviction relief.

